<TD>
<P>At 6 months (T2) 2 out of 8 subscales on the Parent Report yielded statistically significant before/after or between-group results.<BR/>Total Behaviour Problems: I (n = 23) = before: 55.87 (SD 12.07) versus after: 50.87 (SD 9.62), t = 2.89, P &lt; 0.005, ES = 0.41.<BR/>Social Subscale: C (n = 18) = before: 42.22 (SD 8.33) versus after: 39 (SD 11.23), t = 2.24, P &lt; 0.05, ES = -0.39.<BR/>
</P>
</TD>
<TD>
<P>At 9 months (T3) 4 out of 8 subscales on the Parent Report yielded statistically significant before/after or between-group results:<BR/>Total Behavior Problems: I (n = 23) = before: 56.61 (SD 11.28) versus after: 50.30 (SD 10.63), t = 3.22, P &lt; 0.005, ES = 0.56.<BR/>Internalizing Behavior Problems: I (n = 23) = before: 55.96 (SD 12.81) versus after: 51.87 (SD 10.13), t = 1.85, P &lt; 0.01, ES = 0.32.<BR/>Externalizing Behavior Problems: I (n = 23) = before: 54.30 (SD. 11.01) versus after: 48.30 (SD 11.13), t = 3.44, P &lt; 0.005, ES = 0.55.<BR/>School Subscale: I (n = 19) = before: 46.90 (SD 8.99) versus after: 49.79 (SD 4.43), t = -1.94, P &lt; 0.05, ES = 0.32.<BR/>
